Title: HO61508 and H2HO Ontologies

Overview

HO61508: A modular hazard ontology aligned with IEC 61508 (hazard analysis phase).
H2HO: A hydrogen-specific extension of HO61508, conceptually aligned with ISO 15916.
See the paper for detailed concepts, design rationale, and evaluation.
Repository contents

ho61508.ttl — Hazard Ontology 61508 (HO61508).
ho61508-overview.graph — Overview graph for HO61508.
h2ho.ttl — Hydrogen Hazard Ontology (H2HO) extending HO61508.
h2ho-overview.graph — Overview graph for H2HO.
iso15916-h2ho-mapping.txt — Mapping notes from ISO 15916 terminology to H2HO.
LICENSE — CC BY 4.0 license.
How to use

Open ho61508.ttl and h2ho.ttl in your RDF/OWL tool (e.g., Protégé).
Use them as a base for domain-specific hazard models; see the mapping file for ISO 15916 alignment.
For background and examples, consult the paper.
